What is the output of the following C program?
#include <stdio.h>
int main() {
    char str[] = "NEPAL";
    char *ptr = str;
    while (*ptr != '\0') {
        printf("%c", *ptr + 1);
        ptr++;
    }
    printf("\n");
    return 0;
}

What does the following finite automaton accept? (q0 is the start state, q1 is the final state)
States: {q0, q1}
Alphabet: {0, 1}
Transitions: δ(q0, 0) = q0, δ(q0, 1) = q1, δ(q1, 0) = q0, δ(q1, 1) = q1

What is the output of the following C++ code?
#include <iostream>
void func(int x) {
    std::cout << "Integer version" << std::endl;
}
void func(double x) {
    std::cout << "Double version" << std::endl;
}
int main() {
    func(10.5f); // 10.5f is a float
    return 0;
}
